title: For Sale/Trade:  Chinese Type 56 SKS not Norinco
postcontent: MATCHING numbers on all metal parts, including the bolt. This 6 digit /26\ marked Type 56 was likely manufactured just after April 1957, when Jianshe Arsenal first started using the /26\ marking. The carbine has been completely cleaned of Cosmoline down to disassembly of the bolt and cleaning out the firing pin channel. This Type 56 has an unnumbered beechwood stock, reflecting its time in Albania, that has nice fish scale flecking and a single hole buttplate. The stock is solid with a lot of character from various well executed repairs.  This C&R eligible very early Chinese Type 56 SKS was originally provided to Albania as military aid in the early 60’s. These early Chinese SKSs are all milled construction, including the trigger groups, unlike the later Norincos, and have long-lugged threaded barrels. The barrels are also chrome-lined ensuring that these have very good to excellent condition bores! Many SKS collectors and shooters consider these to be the finest quality Chinese SKSs.  Shipping $35 for CONUS (the lower 48 states minus CA). California, Alaska and Hawaii may require extra funds from the buyer for shipping and or paperwork (CA). For those states, I will charge actual shipping (+$10 for CA) and will send you a picture of the UPS receipt showing the actual cost.

This FFL-03/C&R ELIGIBLE very early Chinese Type 56 SKS was originally provided to Albania as military aid in the early 60’s.
